<subSubSection id="3ABA651AA35EB039FF6DED7589A46488" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="721F3691A35EB039FF6DED7589A46488" blockId="5.[151,1436,671,1420]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A35EB039FF6DED758D016460" bold="true" box="[198,319,1354,1380]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A35EB039FDD9ED748F116460" authorityName="Matsumura, Nusillard" authorityYear="2007" box="[626,815,1354,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubroguttatus">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A35EB039FDD9ED748EBF6460" box="[626,641,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A35EB039FD24ED748F116460" box="[655,815,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">rubroguttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A35EB039FCC2ED74881A6460" authorityName="Webb &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2007" box="[873,1060,1354,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unimaculatus">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A35EB039FCC2ED748F466460" box="[873,888,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A35EB039FC2DED74881A6460" box="[902,1060,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">unimaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the male genitalia but can be distinguished by its slightly more robust aedeagal shaft in lateral view with basal flanges less well developed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
